{
  "texts": [
    "While there is ongoing work to improve path coverage without modifying the application, these solutions are not yet ready for real industrial problems.",
    "The challenge of linking new HYPTA methods to certification processes also remains unresolved [86].Conversely, our approach employs a black-box testing methodology utilizing GA and RL.",
    "This method does not require detailed knowledge of hardware and software.",
    "Moreover, GA and RL efficiently explore the solution space, minimizing the need for extensive execution time measurements and data collection, thereby enhancing the efficiency and reliability of the testing process.",
    "Usage of ML in WCET AnalysisRecent studies have highlighted the potential of ML in overcoming the limitations of static analysis by adapting to complex software and hardware interactions [87,88,20]."
  ]
}